      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increased benefit amounts create a \"welfare trap\" where earning even a small wage causes a sharp reduction in total income due to clawback provisions, effectively making work financially unattractive. This structural design discourages labor force participation by removing the economic incentive to seek employment when benefits are already high. While some programs have implemented work mandates to mitigate this, the core issue remains the high replacement rates that undermine the fundamental purpose of a safety net.",
